1
00:00:00,375 --> 00:00:02,460
This is how I want to celebrate my birthday.

2
00:00:02,502 --> 00:00:04,129
Listening to the waves, and...

3
00:00:04,170 --> 00:00:05,547
staring up at the clouds.

4
00:00:05,588 --> 00:00:06,798
Happy birthday, Jao!

5
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:07,841
Make a wish.

6
00:00:07,882 --> 00:00:09,633
Happy birthday to your mom, too.

7
00:00:09,634 --> 00:00:11,301
I know what my mom would wish for.

8
00:00:11,302 --> 00:00:11,928
Do you see that?

9
00:00:11,929 --> 00:00:12,971
[JAO] Around here,

10
00:00:13,012 --> 00:00:16,307
if you own a boat that big, it means you’re pretty well-off.

11
00:00:16,349 --> 00:00:17,350
[JAO] See that ocean?

12
00:00:17,392 --> 00:00:18,560
That’s my playground.

13
00:00:18,601 --> 00:00:20,145
I’m from Siargao!

14
00:00:20,186 --> 00:00:23,063
[JAO] I’m glad I went back here because…

15
00:00:23,064 --> 00:00:24,566
when I was in Manila,

16
00:00:24,607 --> 00:00:26,818
I kept dreaming about this place.

17
00:00:26,860 --> 00:00:29,361
Like it kept calling me back.

18
00:00:29,362 --> 00:00:30,696
[QUINITO] Let me help you out, brother.

19
00:00:30,697 --> 00:00:31,906
Can I ask you a question?

20
00:00:31,948 --> 00:00:32,948
Do you like Pearl?

21
00:00:32,949 --> 00:00:33,742
Why do you ask?

22
00:00:33,783 --> 00:00:35,076
Because I like Pearl.

23
00:00:35,118 --> 00:00:36,118
Oh.

24
00:00:36,119 --> 00:00:38,036
Is it okay if I court Pearl?

25
00:00:38,037 --> 00:00:39,330
It’s up to you, brother.

26
00:00:39,372 --> 00:00:40,874
And of course, it’s up to Pearl.

27
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:42,292
How’d you end up in Siargao?

28
00:00:42,333 --> 00:00:43,542
I was running away.

29
00:00:43,543 --> 00:00:46,462
[JAO] You ran away from Manila to come to Siargao.

30
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:49,882
And I ran away from Siargao to Manila.

31
00:00:49,883 --> 00:00:51,092
We switched places.

32
00:00:51,134 --> 00:00:52,635
So…?

33
00:00:53,178 --> 00:00:54,429
-All right. Uh… -All right.

34
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:55,472
Thank you for everything, Kara.

35
00:00:55,513 --> 00:00:56,681
[SIARGAONON] You’re welcome, Jao.

36
00:00:56,931 --> 00:00:57,932
[JAO] Nice meeting you.

37
00:00:58,183 --> 00:00:59,476
[KARA] Nice knowing you, too.

38
00:01:01,352 --> 00:01:02,353
Jao!

39
00:01:06,566 --> 00:01:07,567
What?

40
00:01:26,294 --> 00:01:28,004
[KARA WHISPERS] Please stay.

41
00:01:38,348 --> 00:01:39,557
What is it?

42
00:01:41,518 --> 00:01:42,519
Nothing.

43
00:01:44,521 --> 00:01:46,231
I just wanted to tell you,

44
00:01:47,273 --> 00:01:48,983
in case I never see you again,

45
00:01:50,109 --> 00:01:53,029
wherever life takes you,

46
00:01:54,781 --> 00:01:57,116
never forget

47
00:02:00,578 --> 00:02:02,163
you’re a Siargaonon.

48
00:02:03,289 --> 00:02:05,291
And you’ll always have a home here.

49
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:18,221
[SIARGAONON] Thank you so much, Kara.

50
00:02:20,473 --> 00:02:21,599
[JAO] Thank you.

51
00:02:27,856 --> 00:02:28,857
See you?

52
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,149
Yeah.

53
00:02:30,567 --> 00:02:31,568
Take care.

54
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:42,287
[KARA SIGHS]

55
00:02:44,038 --> 00:02:48,543
[ALON BY JL]

56
00:04:03,368 --> 00:04:05,369
- [PEARL] Wow! - [ARIEL] What a feast!

57
00:04:05,370 --> 00:04:07,372
- [QUINITO] Let's eat. - [PEARL] So much food!

58
00:04:07,997 --> 00:04:10,291
[PEARL] What’s the occasion? Is it your birthday, Quinito?

59
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:12,460
[HAN BIN] No, it’s not his birthday.

60
00:04:12,502 --> 00:04:14,212
But today, we will celebrate.

61
00:04:14,253 --> 00:04:15,421
Why?

62
00:04:16,422 --> 00:04:17,715
It’s my monthsary on the island.

63
00:04:18,549 --> 00:04:20,051
That’s something you celebrate?

64
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:20,885
Of course!

65
00:04:20,927 --> 00:04:23,470
One month of hanging out with all of you guys

66
00:04:23,471 --> 00:04:25,473
is worth celebrating.

67
00:04:26,099 --> 00:04:28,351
And I want to thank all of you guys for

68
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:30,186
welcoming me into your circle.

69
00:04:30,561 --> 00:04:32,230
[SIARGAONON] Thank you so much.

70
00:04:32,271 --> 00:04:33,314
To all of you.

71
00:04:33,356 --> 00:04:36,526
- Happy one month! - Happy one month on the island, Quinito!

72
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:38,236
- Yeah! - Since you came here,

73
00:04:38,277 --> 00:04:40,279
all we eat is <i>kilaw</i>!

74
00:04:40,530 --> 00:04:42,031
That’s so true!

75
00:04:42,490 --> 00:04:43,992
Special thanks to you.

76
00:04:46,869 --> 00:04:48,495
Uh... Pearl...

77
00:04:48,496 --> 00:04:49,706
Can we talk?

78
00:04:50,748 --> 00:04:51,582
Sure.

79
00:04:51,583 --> 00:04:54,210
Han Bin <i>oppa</i>, did you cook all of this?

80
00:04:55,336 --> 00:04:56,379
Hey, Han Bin <i>oppa</i>!

81
00:04:59,048 --> 00:05:00,341
[ARIEL] I think we should eat.

82
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,681
Pearl.

83
00:05:08,516 --> 00:05:10,810
I’ve been meaning to tell you this, just to make it clear.

84
00:05:15,773 --> 00:05:16,774
I like you.

85
00:05:17,483 --> 00:05:18,860
I like you a lot.

86
00:05:19,277 --> 00:05:20,695
And just so there’s no confusion,

87
00:05:20,737 --> 00:05:21,863
I want to date you.

88
00:05:26,284 --> 00:05:28,161
[PEARL LAUGHS] Are you hungover?

89
00:05:28,202 --> 00:05:29,787
[PEARL LAUGHS]

90
00:05:30,329 --> 00:05:31,872
Hungover or not,

91
00:05:31,873 --> 00:05:33,666
that doesn’t make me like you less.

92
00:05:38,212 --> 00:05:39,797
Thank you…?

93
00:05:44,927 --> 00:05:46,637
Quinito…

94
00:05:47,638 --> 00:05:48,765
you’re kind.

95
00:05:50,016 --> 00:05:51,559
You’re really cute.

96
00:05:52,894 --> 00:05:54,312
[PEARL] You’re charming.

97
00:05:55,271 --> 00:05:58,232
And it’s a bonus that you're an amazing cook.

98
00:06:01,652 --> 00:06:06,574
I’m sure plenty of girls like you.

99
00:06:07,158 --> 00:06:10,161
The only girl that I like is you, Pearl.

100
00:06:20,088 --> 00:06:21,089
Quinito…

101
00:06:25,093 --> 00:06:27,303
I’m just not ready to date anyone.

102
00:06:31,224 --> 00:06:33,434
Look...

103
00:06:34,560 --> 00:06:36,187
The world is so big.

104
00:06:38,064 --> 00:06:40,441
There are still so many cultures I want to experience

105
00:06:40,483 --> 00:06:43,569
and I’m sure I’ll meet a lot more people.

106
00:06:48,699 --> 00:06:50,743
People can say whatever they want,

107
00:06:50,785 --> 00:06:53,746
but I just do know for a fact...

108
00:06:55,706 --> 00:06:58,209
that I’m meant for more than this island life.

109
00:07:00,169 --> 00:07:01,170
Wow, Pearl.

110
00:07:02,338 --> 00:07:04,422
I don’t know how you managed to break my heart

111
00:07:04,423 --> 00:07:06,759
but make me like you more at the same time.

112
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:09,345
You’re so real.

113
00:07:09,762 --> 00:07:10,555
I mean,

114
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,516
I hope I can get to know you more.

115
00:07:16,060 --> 00:07:17,103
Is that fine?

116
00:07:23,359 --> 00:07:24,819
Quinito...

117
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:28,156
As friends only, okay?

118
00:07:33,327 --> 00:07:34,412
Okay?

119
00:07:35,037 --> 00:07:36,122
Friends?

120
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:38,040
Friends.

121
00:07:41,502 --> 00:07:42,502
Guys!

122
00:07:42,503 --> 00:07:45,214
No more talking! Food is here!

123
00:07:45,256 --> 00:07:46,424
What are we waiting for?

124
00:07:46,591 --> 00:07:47,675
[SIARGAONON] Let’s eat!

125
00:07:52,013 --> 00:07:53,222
[ARIEL] Han Bin <i>oppa</i>!

126
00:07:53,556 --> 00:07:55,266
Han Bin <i>oppa</i>! Look.

127
00:07:55,892 --> 00:07:57,268
What’s the meaning of this?

128
00:07:57,602 --> 00:07:58,603
Let me see.

129
00:07:59,103 --> 00:08:00,605
[KOREAN] <i>Cheol, daebak.</i> Wow, that's crazy.

130
00:08:00,646 --> 00:08:03,107
[KOREAN] <i>Jeogeo Park Hanbin aniya? Pillipin-inga?</i> Isn't that Park Hanbin? Is this the Philippines?

131
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,149
That’s nothing.

132
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:06,152
Just some nonsense.

133
00:08:06,194 --> 00:08:07,195
Delete it.

134
00:08:08,321 --> 00:08:09,530
Actually, Ariel,

135
00:08:10,114 --> 00:08:11,239
if you don’t mind,

136
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,950
you can edit me out of the video.

137
00:08:13,701 --> 00:08:14,493
Uh...

138
00:08:14,619 --> 00:08:16,621
But you’re hardly in the video.

139
00:08:17,079 --> 00:08:19,081
I uploaded it because of Pearl.

140
00:08:19,123 --> 00:08:20,291
I know, but...

141
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:22,126
just edit me out please.

142
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,669
I’m a private person.

143
00:08:24,295 --> 00:08:26,297
And I don’t want my face on the Internet.

144
00:08:26,339 --> 00:08:28,257
There’s a monk in Nepal

145
00:08:28,299 --> 00:08:30,885
who told me about evil eye.

146
00:08:30,927 --> 00:08:32,094
Evil eye?

147
00:08:32,470 --> 00:08:34,472
The belief that

148
00:08:34,514 --> 00:08:36,514
someone could be jealous of you and

149
00:08:36,515 --> 00:08:37,725
wish you harm?

150
00:08:37,892 --> 00:08:38,893
Correct!

151
00:08:39,060 --> 00:08:40,061
Oh!

152
00:08:40,228 --> 00:08:42,313
That’s why you don’t want to be on social media?

153
00:08:42,355 --> 00:08:43,356
Yes.

154
00:08:43,606 --> 00:08:45,191
Anyway, let’s eat.

155
00:08:45,650 --> 00:08:46,275
Uh...

156
00:08:46,276 --> 00:08:48,402
No. I think there’s something more.

157
00:08:51,239 --> 00:08:52,031
Uhm...

158
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,865
I think you’re hiding something from us.

159
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:54,867
Tell me honestly.

160
00:08:55,159 --> 00:08:56,827
- What? - Are you hiding something from us?

161
00:08:56,869 --> 00:08:57,662
What?

162
00:08:57,912 --> 00:08:59,080
What are you talking about?

163
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:00,414
I’m just a private person.

164
00:09:00,957 --> 00:09:03,251
You told us that you travelled around Asia.

165
00:09:03,960 --> 00:09:04,961
Maybe...

166
00:09:05,127 --> 00:09:07,545
Maybe you broke someone’s heart in Cambodia.

167
00:09:07,546 --> 00:09:08,339
[HAN BIN SCOFFS]

168
00:09:08,340 --> 00:09:09,340
Or maybe…

169
00:09:09,382 --> 00:09:10,382
You...

170
00:09:10,383 --> 00:09:11,716
You have

171
00:09:11,717 --> 00:09:13,511
lots of enemies in Thailand

172
00:09:13,552 --> 00:09:15,137
and you’re running away from them.

173
00:09:15,179 --> 00:09:16,013
[HAN BIN] Mm-hm.

174
00:09:16,055 --> 00:09:17,515
Or maybe...

175
00:09:17,807 --> 00:09:21,102
you owe money to people in Vietnam!

176
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:24,021
Or maybe you were a monk in Laos

177
00:09:24,063 --> 00:09:27,066
and then you quit because you don’t like the food in the temple.

178
00:09:28,234 --> 00:09:30,236
Or maybe you were—

179
00:09:30,945 --> 00:09:31,654
Oh!

180
00:09:31,696 --> 00:09:34,282
Maybe you have a wife and kids in Korea?

181
00:09:34,615 --> 00:09:36,783
- Oh, my god, Han Bin <i>oppa</i>! - Or maybe...

182
00:09:36,784 --> 00:09:38,410
I’m just a normal Korean guy,

183
00:09:38,411 --> 00:09:40,204
who travelled around Asia but

184
00:09:40,246 --> 00:09:41,831
fell in love in the Philippines,

185
00:09:41,872 --> 00:09:43,749
so I decided to stay here,

186
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:47,169
start a business, make friends I treat like family,

187
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,505
except for one crazy person,

188
00:09:49,547 --> 00:09:51,424
who doesn’t know what he’s talking about.

189
00:09:51,465 --> 00:09:52,466
Case closed!

190
00:09:52,842 --> 00:09:54,051
- Okay? - Let’s eat?

191
00:09:54,093 --> 00:09:55,678
- [QUINITO] Guys, let's eat! - I’m not crazy! You are!

192
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:57,722
- [PEARL] Let's eat! - [QUINITO] We'll finish the food.

193
00:09:58,180 --> 00:09:59,390
[PEARL] It’s so good!

194
00:10:00,057 --> 00:10:01,391
Did you make this?

195
00:10:01,392 --> 00:10:02,517
- Of course! - All of this?

196
00:10:02,518 --> 00:10:03,643
- Yeah! - Wow.

197
00:10:03,644 --> 00:10:04,812
[ARIEL] To be continued.

198
00:10:04,854 --> 00:10:05,563
What's your favorite?

199
00:10:05,564 --> 00:10:06,897
- [HAN BIN] Good? - Delicious!

200
00:10:23,372 --> 00:10:27,209
Ariel said you still haven’t eaten.

201
00:10:27,543 --> 00:10:29,628
It’s okay. I’m not hungry.

202
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:33,966
Is this men's clothing?

203
00:10:35,885 --> 00:10:36,886
It could be.

204
00:10:38,929 --> 00:10:40,431
Who’s it for?

205
00:10:41,307 --> 00:10:43,601
No one. I just wanted to try something new.

206
00:10:44,268 --> 00:10:45,978
I could wear it, too.

207
00:10:46,687 --> 00:10:49,648
[CAROL GIGGLES]

208
00:10:49,649 --> 00:10:50,775
What's so funny?

209
00:10:51,859 --> 00:10:54,028
Nothing! I’m just happy!

210
00:10:54,236 --> 00:10:56,071
How thrilling!

211
00:10:56,072 --> 00:10:57,073
Whatever.

212
00:10:57,114 --> 00:10:58,908
[CAROL LAUGHS]

213
00:10:59,450 --> 00:11:01,911
Eat up. The soup will get cold.

214
00:11:01,952 --> 00:11:03,954
- Thanks, Carol. - [CAROL GIGGLES]

215
00:11:23,766 --> 00:11:24,767
Here.

216
00:11:26,936 --> 00:11:29,313
Since you’re not eating, here.

217
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:44,370
He’s in Cebu.

218
00:11:45,746 --> 00:11:46,539
What?

219
00:11:46,956 --> 00:11:48,874
Jao’s in Cebu.

220
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:50,709
That’s what Tantan told me.

221
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:53,879
I wasn't asking.

222
00:11:53,921 --> 00:11:56,006
Maybe not, but you wanted to know!

223
00:11:56,048 --> 00:11:56,924
No...

224
00:11:56,966 --> 00:11:58,467
[CAROL GIGGLES]

225
00:11:59,552 --> 00:12:01,053
Oh, Kara!

226
00:12:01,762 --> 00:12:03,639
You’re impossible, Carol!

227
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:05,057
Come on.

228
00:12:05,099 --> 00:12:06,183
[CAROL CHUCKLES]

229
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:08,561
Don't forget to take a break, okay?

230
00:12:10,104 --> 00:12:11,981
Sometimes I wake up in the middle of the night

231
00:12:12,022 --> 00:12:16,485
and your lights are still on.

232
00:12:18,487 --> 00:12:21,574
I’ve had a lot of rush orders. I just want to get them done.

233
00:12:21,615 --> 00:12:22,824
Oh…

234
00:12:22,825 --> 00:12:25,536
is that a rush order from Jao?

235
00:12:25,870 --> 00:12:28,788
- This is not for Jao! - [CAROL GIGGLES]

236
00:12:28,789 --> 00:12:30,415
Just admit it already!

237
00:12:30,416 --> 00:12:31,916
You miss him!

238
00:12:31,917 --> 00:12:33,419
No! I really don’t.

239
00:12:33,461 --> 00:12:34,462
Why are you—

240
00:12:35,045 --> 00:12:37,338
Come on! Stop denying it!

241
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:38,632
I’m not denying anything!

242
00:12:39,633 --> 00:12:41,844
Every time I say Jao’s name,

243
00:12:41,886 --> 00:12:43,262
you smile.

244
00:12:43,512 --> 00:12:44,555
I’ve seen it— See?

245
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,975
You’re smiling like this!

246
00:12:48,809 --> 00:12:50,727
- So this is smiling? - Yes!

247
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:52,146
You're just trying to hide it.

248
00:12:52,396 --> 00:12:54,398
But I can see it in your eyes.

249
00:12:58,027 --> 00:12:59,028
Hey.

250
00:12:59,695 --> 00:13:03,699
Admitting you miss him won't make you weak.

251
00:13:05,493 --> 00:13:07,410
It wouldn’t make you some damsel in distress.

252
00:13:07,411 --> 00:13:08,871
I don’t miss him!

253
00:13:08,913 --> 00:13:09,497
I really don’t!

254
00:13:09,538 --> 00:13:11,415
It wouldn’t make you a damsel in distress, okay?

255
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:13,834
- I really don’t, Carol! - Oh, please.

256
00:13:13,876 --> 00:13:14,877
You know…

257
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:20,216
You know… We tease each other all the time,

258
00:13:21,342 --> 00:13:22,551
but I love you.

259
00:13:23,594 --> 00:13:24,595
Hmmm?

260
00:13:26,722 --> 00:13:30,226
You’re like family to me.

261
00:13:31,393 --> 00:13:32,520
Just know that

262
00:13:33,145 --> 00:13:34,563
I’m happy

263
00:13:34,980 --> 00:13:36,357
if you’re happy.

264
00:13:37,066 --> 00:13:41,904
- Stop pointing at my heart. - If your heart is happy!

265
00:13:42,029 --> 00:13:43,239
Hey, Kara.

266
00:13:43,697 --> 00:13:46,825
Don’t you think it’s time?

267
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:49,453
Maybe it’s time

268
00:13:51,163 --> 00:13:52,289
to throw it away!

269
00:13:52,873 --> 00:13:54,166
Throw it far away!

270
00:13:55,501 --> 00:13:57,753
Into the ocean! Your trauma.

271
00:13:58,420 --> 00:13:59,213
Whatever it is.

272
00:13:59,214 --> 00:14:01,215
Trauma from your past relationship.

273
00:14:01,840 --> 00:14:02,841
[KARA SIGHS]

274
00:14:03,759 --> 00:14:04,843
[CAROL] Just throw it away.

275
00:14:06,554 --> 00:14:07,263
Hm?

276
00:14:10,266 --> 00:14:11,934
Because when love...

277
00:14:13,227 --> 00:14:14,395
comes,

278
00:14:16,814 --> 00:14:19,024
there’s nothing you can do.

279
00:14:20,568 --> 00:14:21,569
[CAROL SIGHS]

280
00:14:22,570 --> 00:14:23,904
Because love…

281
00:14:28,826 --> 00:14:30,327
[CAROL] …is like the ocean.

282
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:33,372
You can't control it.

283
00:14:33,539 --> 00:14:35,082
You can read it,

284
00:14:35,624 --> 00:14:37,585
ride the waves,

285
00:14:37,668 --> 00:14:39,962
wait for the perfect wave to surf...

286
00:14:40,588 --> 00:14:42,798
but you can’t fight it.

287
00:14:43,132 --> 00:14:44,592
Love is the same.

288
00:14:45,259 --> 00:14:49,471
When it finds you, all you can do is surrender.

289
00:14:49,555 --> 00:14:52,308
It doesn’t care whether you're afraid or not.

290
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:54,518
You have to learn to stay afloat.

291
00:14:54,560 --> 00:14:56,145
And have faith.

292
00:15:01,984 --> 00:15:03,277
Ice candy!

293
00:15:03,611 --> 00:15:05,487
- Ice candy, sir! - No, thank you.

294
00:15:05,696 --> 00:15:07,031
Ice candy!

295
00:15:07,740 --> 00:15:10,034
Sir, would you like an ice candy?

296
00:15:10,284 --> 00:15:10,868
Huh?

297
00:15:12,077 --> 00:15:12,995
Is it good?

298
00:15:12,996 --> 00:15:15,205
- Yes, sir! I made it myself. - You sure?

299
00:15:15,289 --> 00:15:17,291
- It’s really good, sir! - All right, let me try one.

300
00:15:17,333 --> 00:15:18,417
Which one?

301
00:15:18,917 --> 00:15:20,294
Coconut or mango?

302
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:32,473
Boat.

303
00:15:33,015 --> 00:15:34,767
Boat?

304
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:35,643
[JAO CHUCKLES]

305
00:15:35,644 --> 00:15:36,644
Never mind. I just…

306
00:15:36,685 --> 00:15:37,978
suddenly missed someone.

307
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:42,816
Anyway, I’ll buy them all.

308
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:45,944
- Thank you, sir! - Hand them out to the tourists.

309
00:15:46,362 --> 00:15:47,863
Take care!

310
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:51,575
- Free ice candy, sir! - Oh, sure. Thank you!

311
00:15:52,326 --> 00:15:53,702
[VENDOR] Free ice candy, ma’am!

312
00:15:53,744 --> 00:15:56,038
- Free ice candy. - [TOURIST] Yes, thank you.

313
00:15:56,830 --> 00:15:57,831
Thank you!

314
00:16:00,709 --> 00:16:02,086
Thank you, sir!

315
00:16:02,127 --> 00:16:03,128
Thank you!

316
00:16:13,472 --> 00:16:16,350
Before, total 22.

317
00:16:16,809 --> 00:16:17,976
Three hundred...

318
00:16:18,018 --> 00:16:19,186
[DELIVERY GUY] Sir Han!

319
00:16:19,728 --> 00:16:21,105
Your package is here.

320
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:23,148
Finally!

321
00:16:23,399 --> 00:16:24,608
I’ve been waiting for this!

322
00:16:25,484 --> 00:16:28,195
Okay, let me see.

323
00:16:31,907 --> 00:16:33,742
You always keep these in stock.

324
00:16:33,784 --> 00:16:35,285
Of course!

325
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:40,499
[HAN BIN] Wow! Beautiful!

326
00:16:43,669 --> 00:16:45,379
- I’ll take a picture, sir. - Oh, okay!

327
00:16:46,964 --> 00:16:47,548
Thank you.

328
00:16:47,589 --> 00:16:48,966
[SIARGAONON] Thank you very much!

329
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:53,512
Very good nice.

330
00:16:54,638 --> 00:16:56,306
Okay.

331
00:17:02,396 --> 00:17:08,277
[PHONE RINGING]

332
00:17:08,318 --> 00:17:09,319
Yes, sir?

333
00:17:09,361 --> 00:17:11,947
[PAUL ON THE PHONE] <i>Jao, I heard you left Cebu.</i>

334
00:17:12,197 --> 00:17:12,990
Yes, sir.

335
00:17:13,240 --> 00:17:14,241
[PAUL ON THE PHONE] <i>Why?</i>

336
00:17:14,575 --> 00:17:16,159
You told me to take a vacation.

337
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:18,077
[PAUL ON THE PHONE] <i>Yes! In Cebu.</i>

338
00:17:18,078 --> 00:17:19,288
[PAUL ON THE PHONE] <i>Is something wrong?</i>

339
00:17:19,329 --> 00:17:20,956
No, sir. I’m good.

340
00:17:21,457 --> 00:17:22,666
Actually, very good.

341
00:17:23,375 --> 00:17:24,543
I’m back to my old self.

342
00:17:25,043 --> 00:17:26,462
[PAUL ON THE PHONE] <i>So, where are you?</i>

343
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:29,798
Where I should be.

344
00:18:26,188 --> 00:18:27,189
[JAO] Hi, miss!

345
00:19:04,726 --> 00:19:06,103
[KARA] I thought you were in Cebu.

346
00:19:06,144 --> 00:19:07,354
[JAO] I missed you too.

347
00:19:07,813 --> 00:19:08,981
Got any plans tomorrow?

348
00:19:09,189 --> 00:19:10,190
[KARA] Nope.

349
00:19:11,400 --> 00:19:12,359
[JAO] Good.

350
00:19:12,776 --> 00:19:13,819
Are these the mangroves?

351
00:19:13,861 --> 00:19:15,362
- Beautiful. - Ruth, this is Jao.

352
00:19:15,404 --> 00:19:16,780
Hi, Ruth. Nice to meet you!

353
00:19:16,822 --> 00:19:17,489
I’m Jao.

354
00:19:17,531 --> 00:19:19,740
[KARA] Ruth knows everything about me.

355
00:19:19,741 --> 00:19:24,120
All my secrets, fears, doubts…

356
00:19:24,121 --> 00:19:25,038
everything.

357
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:26,039
Ruth wants to say something.

358
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:27,374
She said I should tell you myself.

359
00:19:27,583 --> 00:19:28,375
What is it?

360
00:19:28,417 --> 00:19:30,210
I want more than friendship, Kara.

361
00:19:32,504 --> 00:19:34,673
You know, you look like a K-pop star.

362
00:19:34,715 --> 00:19:36,508
Are you single or taken?

363
00:19:36,550 --> 00:19:39,552
[HAN BIN] I’m single but my heart is already taken.

364
00:19:39,553 --> 00:19:40,846
[JAO] I want to get to know you more.

365
00:19:40,888 --> 00:19:43,682
Like you said, I’ll ride the waves with you.

366
00:19:43,724 --> 00:19:45,726
- Jao! - Hey!
